results.lead_paragraph: 'One at a Time' Museum of Modern Art 11 West 53d Street Manhattan (212) 708-9400 Recommended ages: 5 and up Through May 1, 1993 The emphasis, of course, is on modern artworks, whose playfulness children quickly grasp. The family-art program encourages children to look for the "story" in, say, a Kandinsky. "We try to stimulate a dialogue with art," said Joyce Raimondo, the family program's coordinator. "They're not learning art-historical facts."
